HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar sabbin masu kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar mutane kashi 14 cikin 100 da ke dauke da cutar HIV da kuma AIDS.
Fiye da mutane 820,000 ne ke fama da cutar, kamar yadda jami'an kiwon lafiya suka sanar.
Kimanin sabbin mutane 40,000 aka ba da rahoton cutar a cikin rabin rabin shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtukan sun kamu ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya bambanta da na dā.
A yanzu haka, HIV yana yaduwa da sauri a wasu sassan China daga jinin da aka yi amfani da shi.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya a China a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Ko da yake, shekara shekara, adadin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau a kasar Sin ya karu da 100,000.
Kamuwa da cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i ya zama matsala mai tsanani a tsakanin 'yan luwaɗi a kasar Sin.
A shekarar 1997, an dakatar da haramta luwadi a kasar Sin, amma an ce nuna wariya ga 'yan luwadi ya yi yawa.
Saboda ƙimar da ƙasar take da shi na ra'ayin ɗariƙar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin kamuwa da cutar ta haifar ne daga rashin yin amfani da isassun hanyoyin kariya a wannan jima'i.
Tun daga shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar a wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
